dcterms:description: NASA’s spectral database provides a collection of spectral data for various materials, which was used to select materials with different reflectance values for the experiments in visible light communications.
dcterms:title: NASA’s spectral database

dcterms:description: Channel taps for different hybrid materials were measured in a controlled experimental setup to train neural networks for channel tap prediction in visible light communications.
dcterms:title: Channel taps for different hybrid materials

dcterms:description: Measurements for training and testing the MLP were conducted to evaluate the performance of the neural network in predicting channel taps under various conditions.
dcterms:title: Measurements for training and testing the MLP
